<p><span class="m_first-letter m_first-letter--flagged">T</span>he Scottish government has recorded 1,027 new coronavirus cases and five new deaths. Some 13.5 per cent of tests being carried out are positive.</p>
<p>The figures for new cases in Scotland are slightly below yesterday’s (1,054), but much higher than this time last week (668).</p>
<p>Public Health Wales has recorded 638 new cases and one further death. The number of new cases in Wales is down on yesterday (752) but much higher than the day before (425).</p>
<p>And in Northern Ireland the Department of Health has recorded 923 new cases (up from 828 yesterday) and one further death (the same as yesterday).</p>
