<h3 class="live-post__title">England toll rises by 43</h3>
<div class="articleBodyText section">
<div class="article-body-text component  ">
<div class="component-content">
<p><span class="m_first-letter m_first-letter--flagged">A</span> further 43 people who tested positive for coronavirus have died in hospital in England, bringing the total number of confirmed deaths reported in hospitals to 30,323, NHS England said on Thursday.</p>
<p>Patients were aged between 32 and 99 years old. All but one patient, aged 71, had known underlying health conditions.</p>
<p>The deaths were between August 10 and October 7. Most were on or after October 6.</p>
<p>Eight other deaths were reported with no positive Covid-19 test result.</p>
