<div class="live-post__wrapper-body-article">
<h3 class="live-post__title">Poland makes wearing masks outside compulsory as cases climb</h3>
<div class="articleBodyText section">
<div class="article-body-text component  ">
<div class="component-content">
<p><span class="m_first-letter m_first-letter--flagged">W</span>earing masks outside will be compulsory across the whole of Poland from October 10, the Prime Minister said on Thursday, as the country grapples with a sharp spike in coronavirus cases.</p>
<p>&quot;The second wave has reached us and we have face it in a decisive way,&quot; Mateusz Morawiecki told reporters, explaining that the entire country of 38 million would now be considered a &quot;yellow zone&quot;</p>
<p>The country is some steps away from having a shortage of hospital beds for coronavirus patients, the PM added at a news conference.</p>
<p>However, Mr Morawiecki said that the country will still aim to avoid a total lockdown in an effort to shield the economy.</p>
