<div class="live-post__wrapper-body-article">
<h3 class="live-post__title">Head of Russian Orthodox Church self-isolates  </h3>
<div class="articleBodyText section">
<div class="article-body-text component  ">
<div class="component-content">
<p><span class="m_first-letter m_first-letter--flagged">P</span>atriarch Kirill, the head of the Russian Orthodox Church, has self-isolated after seeing a person who tested positive for Covid-19.</p>
<p>The Russian Orthodox Church said on Thursday that 73-year old Kirill, who leads the world’s second-largest Christian denomination after the Roman Catholic Church in terms of the number of followers, decided not to attend official celebrations this morning due to health precautions.</p>
<p>“The time of my personal self-isolation has not come to an end yet, according to the medical advice I have received,” he said in a statement addressed to the monastery outside Moscow hosting the celebrations.</p>
<p>“I found it impossible to risk infecting all of you.”</p>
</div>
